ABSTRACT:
Pointers are a tool in C programming but they can be hard to understand. This project tries to make pointers easier to understand by showing how they are used in life like in game engines. We look at the basics of pointers how memory works, how to use memory dynamically how to use pointers with structures and how to update data in time.

We use examples from games to show how pointers help with memory management and fast data access. We also write example programs that show how to use pointers to update objects in time handle memory dynamically and make programs run faster.

Our results show that pointers make programs run efficiently and allow for advanced programming techniques that are necessary for making games and other systems.

