INTRODUCTION:
Problem Statement:
It is hard for beginners to understand pointers but they are necessary for making high-performance games.
Background:Pointers allow us to access memory directly which makes it easier to work with data run programs faster and use memory efficiently. Game engines rely heavily on pointers to manage objects, textures, physics and real-time updates.

Objectives:
* To understand the basics of pointers
* To show how pointers are used in game engines
* To make a system that can handle objects in time using pointers
* To see how pointers can improve performance
